{"ts":"2026-05-11","event":"patch_open","id":"wilson-needs-hexa-build-out-of-tree","status":"pending_external","trees":["build-driver","install-layout"],"note":"After G2 binary promotion, `hexa build core/main.hexa` (multi-module wilson) fails: (1) `hexa build` doesn't pre-flatten use/import — only `hexa run`'s aot_build_slot does (via module_loader.hexa) — so app.c has only main.hexa's code + forward-decls -> linker Undefined symbols (reproduced on a trivial 2-file program too). (2) clang -I is <argv0-dir>/self = ~/.hx/bin/self (nonexistent for installed hexa_real) so #include \"runtime.c\" -> file not found; runtime.c is at $HEXA_LANG/self/. (3) minor: module_loader.hexa flatten on stage0 interp is slow (>150s on wilson's ~30-40 module graph). Workarounds: manual module_loader->hexa_v2->clang pipeline, ln -s ~/core/hexa-lang/self ~/.hx/bin/self. Ask: `hexa build` mirror `hexa run`'s flatten->transpile->clang; -I = $HEXA_LANG/self; faster (compiled) flatten or expose aot_build_slot's path. wilson uses the manual pipeline meanwhile.","detail":"patches/wilson-needs-hexa-build-out-of-tree.md","source":"wilson session — hexa build investigation"}
